This article is a statement made by President Obama on the one-year anniversary of the violence in South Sudan. The President expresses his disappointment that the hope and optimism felt when South Sudan became a new nation in 2011 has been overshadowed by bloodshed and tragedy. He appeals to the leaders of South Sudan to pursue peace and end the cycle of violence. The President also urges the people of South Sudan to renew their spirit of hope and unity and seek peaceful reconciliation instead of violent retribution. The United States will continue to support those who seek peace and progress in South Sudan.